name: 6-[bis(5-ethylfuran-2-yl)methyl]-7-nitro-2,3-dihydro-1,4-benzodioxine
source: Karthikeyan M.; Glen R.C.; Bender A. General melting point prediction based on a diverse compound dataset and artificial neural networks. J. Chem. Inf. Model.; 2005; 45(3); 581-2671
Reason: 6-[Bis(5-ethylfuran-2-yl)methyl]-7-nitro-2,3-dihydro-1,4-benzodioxine has a complex structure with multiple functional groups that can influence its melting point. The basic unit is furan, which has a melting point of -12.0 degrees Celsius. The presence of two ethyl groups can increase the melting point due to additional molecular weight and possible hydrogen bonding, estimated to be around +10 degrees Celsius each. The nitro group can also contribute to the melting point due to its electronegativity and potential for dipole-dipole interactions, estimated at around +10 degrees Celsius. The ether linkages can also raise the melting point by approximately +5 degrees Celsius due to additional molecular weight and possible hydrogen bonding. The presence of two methyl groups can lower the melting point due to increased molecular weight and possible hydrogen bonding, estimated to be around -5 degrees Celsius each. The benzodioxine ring can also contribute to the melting point due to its planarity and potential for hydrogen bonding, estimated at around +10 degrees Celsius.
